steinhausler university of salzburg a visiting professor at cisac and iis the european forum and cisac co sponsored workshops on the legal and illegal transport and diversion of hazardous materials and us and eu policy responses to security threats bunn and steinhausler also conducted a cisac project to strengthen global practices for protecting nuclear material against theft and sabotage steinhausler worked closely with scott sagan political science iis senior fellow and participated in cisac's course on international security lyudmila zaitseva a cisac visiting fellow from the national nuclear centre in semipalatinsk kazakhstan worked on documentation and information about nuclear and security issues in the former soviet union in addition steinhausler worked with jim sweeney engineering economic systems operations research on an integrative approach to assessing the impact of the complete nuclear fuel cycle from uranium mining to waste disposal on the environment contact george bunn publications illicit trafficking of weapons usable nuclear material facts and uncertainties lyudmila zaitseva friedrich steinhausler physics and society newsletter vol 33 1 2004 html+ pdf+ cover nuclear smuggling chains suppliers intermediaries and end users lyudmila zaitseva kevin hand american behavioral scientist vol 46 6 2003 html+ pdf+ reducing the threat of nuclear theft and sabotage george bunn matthew bunn iaea international symposium 2002 pdf+ cover raising international standards for protecting nuclear materials from theft and sabotage george bunn the nonproliferation review 2000 pdf+ an alternative framework for the control of nuclear materials robert l rinne cisac 1999 pdf+ search cisac search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mai